-- Pound Extends Decline After U.K. Unemployment Data, BOE Minutes
-- B y   A n c h a l e e   W o r r a c h a t e
-- 2013-04-17T08:39:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-17/pound-extends-decline-after-u-k-unemployment-data-boe-minutes.html
The pound extended a drop against
the dollar and the euro after reports showed unemployment rose
in the three months through February and Bank of England
Governor  Mervyn King  was defeated in a push for more stimulus.  The pound fell 0.3 percent to $1.5316 as of 9:38 a.m. in
London. It dropped 0.4 percent to 86.08 pence per euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anchalee Worrachate in London at 
